title: At least 24 die in suspected gas leak in South Africa
description: At least 24 people have died in South Africa due to a suspected gas leak, local media reported.

title: Disney star and pop singer dies aged 48
description: Coco Lee - a Hong Kong-born singer who starred in Disney's Mulan - has died at the age of 48.

title: Man who carved names into Colosseum says he 'didn't know it was old'
description: The tourist who carved his name into the Colosseum has reportedly claimed in an apology letter that he didn't know it was so old.

title: LIV returns to venue where rebellion started - as golf's future remains unclear despite PGA merger
description: A year after being ostracised by the golfing establishment, the Saudi-funded LIV rebels are back competing in England as they prepare to come in from the cold.

title: Greta Thunberg could face prison after charge of disobeying police order
description: Swedish climate activist Greta Thunberg has been charged with disobeying a police order during a protest in her home country.

title: 'They want to destroy us': Why the Taliban closure of salons is such a huge blow to Afghan women
description: As I stepped into my local beauty salon here in England to have my nails done ahead of my brother's wedding, my phone pinged.

title: Israeli troops complete withdrawal from Jenin refugee camp - but Palestinians' deep hatred has only hardened
description: Jenin refugee camp is a mess.

title: Fundraiser set up for officer charged with killing teen in France closes after £1.2m raised
description: A fundraiser set up for the family of the police officer charged with the killing of Nahel Merzouk in France has raised more than £1.2m, as courts across the country battle to process cases following the recent riots.

title: UK takes Iran to court over Ukrainian passenger jet shot down in 2020
description: The UK is among several nations launching a case against Iran at the United Nations' highest court over the shooting down of a Ukrainian passenger jet and the deaths of all 176 on board in 2020.

title: North Korea's failed satellite was unable to spy on targets, South Korea says
description: North Korea's failed spy satellite's optical device was "poor" in terms of its resolution and for tracing targets, experts from South Korea and the US have declared.

title: Extinction Rebellion activists block holes on 10 golf courses
description: Climate activists have filled in holes at 10 golf courses in a protest at the "waste of water" used to maintain the sport while severe drought grips the nation.

title: 'Code red' alert urges millions to stay inside as rare storm kills one
description: Millions of people across the Netherlands have been warned to stay indoors as a rare summer storm hit the Dutch coast, severely disrupting air and rail travel.

title: Chesney Hawkes told kids he loved them in voice note as plane plunged 20,000ft
description: Singer Chesney Hawkes sent tearful voice notes to his family group chat as the plane he was on suddenly plunged 20,000ft.

title: Why Russia's statements about Ukrainian nuclear plant are deeply worrying
description: It was a nerve-wracking night for Ukrainians and the anxiety goes on.

title: Ukraine claims 'explosive devices' planted on roof of Zaporizhzhia nuclear facility
description: Ukraine has claimed "explosive devices" have been placed on the roof of the Zaporizhzhia nuclear power station, as Volodymyr Zelenskyy warned of "dangerous provocations" at the facility.

title: Israel begins withdrawing troops from Jenin as Gaza is hit by airstrikes
description: Israeli troops have begun withdrawing from the West Bank city of Jenin after a two-day operation that left 13 Palestinians dead - as residents of Gaza say the territory has been hit by airstrikes.

title: Elephants may vary what they eat for dinner just like humans, study says
description: Elephants may vary what they eat for dinner every night just like humans, a study suggests.
